snippet.textDisplay:
There is this low budget movie called SEAL Patrol (2014) and getting the combat right was important to them, AND there is also a good amount of vfx in the last half, so it seems right up your league to react to!!
(This movie ain't great. I know one of the actors in the movie, and he's awesome and the guys at the heart of it mean well, but it was made with no budget as sort of a "let's all go to Utah and shoot some guns, Boys!" It was originally called Blackjacks since it's a team of retired special forces and they're CALLED the Blackjacks, but some production company or distributor said "Change the name to SEAL patrol, sounds more military group." while none of them were seals, nor do they patrol. lol)

snippet.textDisplay:
Some of the best Jackie Chan stunt scenes (IMO!):

1) Clocktower fall - Project A
2) Hovercraft sequence (including a foot cast painted like a trainer!) - Rumble In The Bronx
3) Helicopter sequence (this one is amazing, considering no fake helicopters were used!) - Police Story 3

I'm sure others will have mentioned the skyscraper slide from Who Am I?, the stepladder fight from Police Story 4, and the pole slide from Police Story 1.

snippet.textDisplay:
I love these react videos. Sam and Niko are old buddies of mine. But my lord does this dude suck. Tone deaf, cocky, conceited, vanilla, and “the tony hawk” of parkour. Lots of not-so-humble brags. There are loads of enormously talented artists and stuntmen that have been on Corridor’s stuff and handle it with far more tact and consideration for their crews. Meanwhile this guy is endlessly bragging about some shitty episode of Hawaii 5-0. “No wire there”. No sense of humor about The Office. All about how great he is.

Get over yourself, man.
